HEADWORD: Edit
<hw>Ed"it</hw> <pr>(⟦ecr⟧d"⟦icr⟧t)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Edited</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Editing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧diter</ets>, or L. <ets>editus</ets>, p. p. of
<ets>edere</ets> to give out, put forth, publish; <ets>e</ets> out +
<ets>dare</ets> to give. See <er>Date</er> a point of time.]</ety>
<def>To superintend the publication of; to revise and prepare for
publication; to select, correct, arrange, etc., the matter of, for
publication; <as>as, to <ex>edit</ex> a newspaper</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Philosophical treatises which have never been
<qex>edited</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Enfield.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>edited</ent>⟦br⟧
